## Executive Summary

As the lead Enterprise Architect on the Unified Service Management Platform project, I directed the end-to-end architectural design of a cloud-based IT service desk and change management system intended to replace an existing vendor-dependent solution. Following TOGAF ADM phases, I conducted requirements analysis, validated business drivers, and designed a scalable microservices architecture deployed on private infrastructure, addressing critical organizational constraints including data residency compliance and cost optimization.

**Key Outcome:** A production-grade Solutions Design Document (SDD) approved for implementation, supporting a 10x growth trajectory while reducing operational licensing costs by transitioning from vendor dependency to an internally managed platform.

