## Key Decisions & Trade-Offs

### Trade-Off 1: Complexity vs. Scalability
- **Decision:** Microservices architecture
- **Trade-off:** Operational complexity (service discovery, distributed debugging) increased
- **Mitigation:** OpenShift orchestration handles most operational burden; investment in monitoring/logging infrastructure

### Trade-Off 2: Open-Source vs. Vendor Support
- **Decision:** .NET, PostgreSQL, Kafka (open-source stack)
- **Trade-off:** No vendor SLA; team must manage patches/security
- **Mitigation:** Community support, industry adoption, internal ESSM team capacity

### Trade-Off 3: Upfront Complexity vs. Long-Term Flexibility
- **Decision:** Domain-driven service decomposition
- **Trade-off:** Higher initial design/deployment effort
- **Mitigation:** Yields faster time-to-value through independent team delivery

